A:

var result = myList.FirstOrDefault(x => x.Name == "foo");

If you need to return null if there's no match, use FirstOrDefault instead of First. If you need to throw an exception if there's no match, use Single instead of First.
Note that this will only work for single items in your list. If you have multiple items with the same name, then you'll need to use something else (like Distinct) to remove duplicates first.

